I have been reading through the link that you posted and have been playing arround with the formula to compare 2 warriors of the same level but with different stamina.<br>
<br>
General formula: <br>
[(300+Stamina)*Level*Levelmultiplier]/300 = Hitpoints <br>
<br>
In reverse, we get: <br>
([ Hitpoints * 300 ] ) / ([ 300 + Stamina ] * Level) = Levelmultiplier <br>
<br>
Level 13 warrior, the Level Modifier as stated on the post is 22. One warrior has 85 stamina the other 100.<br>
<br>
((300 + 85)*13*22) / 300 = 367<br>
((300 + 100)*13*22) / 300 = 381<br>
<br>
Level 35<br>
((300 + 85)*35*25) / 300 = 1122<br>
((300 +100)*35*25) / 300 = 1166<br>
<br>
Level 45<br>
((300 + 85)*45*27) / 300 = 1559<br>
((300 +100)*45*27) / 300 = 1620<br>
<br>
Level 55<br>
((300 + 85)*55*2<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   / 300 = 1976<br>
